
===================================
📌 1. Finglish Version (Persian Latin Script)
===================================

📖 **Tashrih:**
    Dastoor `arm2hpdl` baraye tabdil filehaye ARM assembly be formati ke baraye dastgah haye chapgar (printer) HP printer-ha ghabele fahm bashad estefade mishavad. Be ebarate digar, in dastoor komak mikonad code assembly ro chap konid.

⚙️ **Gozine-ha:**
    🔹 `arm2hpdl file.s`  --> 📄 Tabdil file assembly `file.s` be formati ke baraye chap monaseb bashad.
    🔹 `arm2hpdl -o output.hpdl file.s` --> 💾 Save kardan natijeh tabdil shode dar file `output.hpdl`.
    🔹 `arm2hpdl -landscape file.s` --> 🔄 Chap kardan be soorate ofoghi (landscape).
    🔹 `arm2hpdl -portrait file.s` --> 🧍 Chap kardan be soorate amoodi (portrait).

🛠 **Mesal-ha:**

    $ arm2hpdl code.s

    🔹 Tabdil file assembly `code.s` va namayesh natijeh dar terminal.

    $ arm2hpdl -o output.hpdl code.s

    🔹 Tabdil file assembly `code.s` va zakhireh natijeh dar file `output.hpdl`.  In file mishe be printer HP ferestade she.

✅ **Mesal sade:**

    $ arm2hpdl -landscape code.s > print.hpdl

    🔹 Tabdil file assembly `code.s` be soorate ofoghi va zakhireh natijeh dar file `print.hpdl`.  Badesh file `print.hpdl` mitoone chap beshe.

===================================
📌 2. English Version
===================================

📖 **Description:**
    The `arm2hpdl` command converts ARM assembly files into a format suitable for HP printers (HP Printer Description Language). In essence, it helps you print your assembly code.

⚙️ **Options:**
    🔹 `arm2hpdl file.s`  --> 📄 Convert the assembly file `file.s` to a printable format.
    🔹 `arm2hpdl -o output.hpdl file.s` --> 💾 Save the converted output to the file `output.hpdl`.
    🔹 `arm2hpdl -landscape file.s` --> 🔄 Print in landscape orientation.
    🔹 `arm2hpdl -portrait file.s` --> 🧍 Print in portrait orientation.

🛠 **Examples:**

    $ arm2hpdl code.s

    🔹 Converts the assembly file `code.s` and displays the output in the terminal.

    $ arm2hpdl -o output.hpdl code.s

    🔹 Converts the assembly file `code.s` and saves the output to the file `output.hpdl`. This file can then be sent to an HP printer.

✅ **Simple Example:**

    $ arm2hpdl -landscape code.s > print.hpdl

    🔹 Converts the assembly file `code.s` to landscape orientation and saves the output to the file `print.hpdl`. The `print.hpdl` file can then be printed.
